<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2018/04/23/dependency-management-plugin-1-0-5-release">Dependency Management Plugin 1.0.5.RELEASE</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/8d143bf6d465cb98f8196cf4311256d0?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/awilkinson">Andy Wilkinson</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2018-04-23 14:13:39.518">April 23, 2018</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3257" href="/blog/2018/04/23/dependency-management-plugin-1-0-5-release#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>I am pleased to announce that <a href="https://github.com/spring-gradle-plugins/dependency-management-plugin">Gradle dependency management plugin</a> 1.0.5.RELEASE is now available from Maven Central, Bintray, and the <a href="https://plugins.gradle.org/plugin/io.spring.dependency-management">Gradle Plugin Portal</a>. This maintenance release fixes a <a href="https://github.com/spring-gradle-plugins/dependency-management-plugin/milestone/25?closed=1">handful of issues</a>. It was included in the recent Spring Boot 1.5.12 and 2.0.1 releases and is also a recommended upgrade for all other users of the plugin.</p>
</div>
</section>
